ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would recommend it to any graduate student with interests in ethics, political philosophy, or the history of philosophy.I'd recommend it to undergraduates with adequate preparation, with the qualification that the discussion level was very high and those without a serious interest in the topic are likely to struggle to follow it all. It's not an course for those interested in finding out what Hobbes and Kant thought but who lack philosophical background.
Yes, I'd recommend philosophy 650 to fellow students: great course, great professor.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Learning more about philosophy always deepens my knowledge of the discipline!I don't know what my dissertation topic is yet, so I can't answer the second question.
Yes, in profound and important ways; yes.
